metadata.name: Ripple / Cymatic #221
metadata.description:
Mathematical animations inspired by cymatics.  

Symmetric waves ripple around a boundary, causing infinitely complex patterns that evolve forever but never repeat.

Variations are the frequencies and amplitudes of waves, the boundary shape, and the velocity of phase shifts.

Some are contained, others escape to infinity.

metadata.name: Glass Marble #51
metadata.description:
Pixels create a glass marble effect
Capture taken at 14 seconds.
Lots of possible combinations of colors, size of marble and the oscillation directions will vary.

Some outputs look like orbs or planets

50% of royalties go to the first minter to thank you all for my wonderful FXHash journey so far. 



Made using Hydra
@HicPunks

metadata.name: Caterpillars #44
metadata.description:
DISCLAIMER : 
I have started coding about 4 months ago and I am not very good at this. I have tried to clean up the code as best as I could, and I hope that there is nothing terribly wrong left inside. 

This will be kind of a charity project where the PRIMARY SALES will be 
divided as follows:
 - 60 % of primary sales will go to "Askida Fatura" -> https://askidafatura.ibb.gov.tr/
 - 20 % will go to Processing Foundation -> https://processingfoundation.org/
 - 20 % will go to Coding Train -> https://twitter.com/thecodingtrain

"Askida Fatura" is run by Istanbul Municipality and is a campaign that is used for paying the utility bills of the less fortunate living in Istanbul. On average, a couple of tezos pays one bill, and I hope to pay 5 - 10 bills with this.

I will figure out the best way to transfer the amounts later this week and the upcoming weeks, and will provide proof of transfer via my twitter. 

SINCE THIS IS CHARITY, I WILL NOT BE BURNING THE REMAINING EDITIONS!!!

Still, if you dont like what you got ping me and you can get your refund. 

twitter : https://twitter.com/evilnft
fxhash : https://www.fxhash.xyz/u/evilnft
objkt : https://objkt.com/profile/evilnft/created

about Caterpillars,

This is a humble project, does not try to achieve too much, and also wants you to not expect too much from it. 

features : 
 - 8 palettes
 - 2 different origins
 - 5 different characters
 - 6 to 49 sections
 - should be responsive, although I have only tested this on computers...

 press "s" to save a png.

metadata.name: Fractured Cells #37
metadata.description:
Poisson disc sampling of a noise field masked to a shape, and then Voronoi tessellation. Rendered in hand-drawn lines.

Press 's' to take a screenshot. The image size is 1000x1000. 

Features
- 48 curated possible palettes
- 4 possible color distribution methods
- 3 possible shapes: one circle, random circles, circles distributed based on a quadtree 
- 1 to 3 levels of polygon smoothing
- polygon outlines
- polygon fill density and direction
- hand-drawn line roughness

Rare features
- 1 circle
- no polygon smoothing
- background polygons offset from foreground
- color distribution to have a "striped" appearance
